      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Vignetted upper-body shot of a young man in three-quarter profile. He is dressed in a formal suit with a necktie.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Milorad Petrović (1865, Šabac – 1928, Skopje) was a Serbian actor at the Royal Serbian National Theatre in Belgrade. He also played the leading role in the first Serbian silent film, 'Life and Deeds of Immortal Vožd Karađorđe', in 1911. The photograph was a gift to his former landlady.</ab>
